Data

Load selected data based on 03_codebook

data_included_documented = read.csv(file = "data_included_documented.csv")[,-1]

Analysis

If the model does not converge, we will first exclude the random slope for country. If the model does still not converge, we will subsequently exclude the random intercept for country. Instead we will z-standardize outcomes separately for each country.

Preferred Relationship Options

H1a Interest in Single Life

H1a There is a negative linear link between right-wing political orientation and womens interest in being single.
Outcome: Ratings for interest in single life. Predictor: Political Orientation. Random intercept and random slope for country.

Models
#model_interest_single <- lmer(interest_single ~ political_orientation + (1+political_orientation|country), data = data_included_documented)

Political, ethnic and religious similarity

H2a Preference for similarity in political beliefs

H2a There is no linear link between right-wing political orientation and womens preferences for partners similar political beliefs and values when controlling for a quadratic link. There is a positive quadratic link between right-wing political orientation and womens preferences for partners similar political beliefs and values when controlling for a linear link. Outcome: Preference ratings for partners similar political beliefs and values. Predictor: Political Orientation. Random intercept and random slope for country.

Models
model_pref_politicalsim = lmer(pref_politicalsim ~ political_orientation + I(political_orientation^2) +
                                 (1+political_orientation|country),
                               data = data_included_documented)

effects1 = lmer(pref_politicalsim ~ political_orientation + (1 | country),
             data = data_included_documented) %>%
  allEffects(confidence.level = 0.997, xlevels = 49) %>%
  as.data.frame()

effects1 = as.data.frame(effects1$political_orientation)

n = data_included_documented %>%
  filter(!is.na(pref_politicalsim)) %>%
  count()

plot1 = ggplot() +
  geom_jitter(data = data_included_documented, aes(x = political_orientation, y = pref_politicalsim),
              alpha = 0.05) +
  geom_line(data = effects1, aes(x = political_orientation, y = fit)) +
  geom_ribbon(data = effects1, aes(x = political_orientation, ymin = lower, ymax = upper),
              fill = brewer.pal(9,"Blues")[8], alpha = 0.8) +
  scale_x_continuous(name = "Political Orientation") +
  scale_y_continuous(name = "Importance\nPolitical Similarity",
                     limits = c(-0.5,6.5),
                     breaks = c(0,1,2,3,4,5,6)) +
  ggtitle(paste0(
      "H2a Preference for similarity in political beliefs (n = ",
      prettyNum(n$n, big.mark = ",", preserve.width = "none"),
      ")"))
plot1
## Warning: Removed 308 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
